external.description:
AI 기술의 진화가 인간 고유의 사고능력을 어디까지 따라올 수 있는지에 대한 궁금증이 고조되고 있다. 인공지능의 발전 양상을 바라보는 시선 속에서, 인간과 AI 사이의 미묘한 경계가 다시 한 번 도마에 올랐다. 



KBS LIFE와 UHD Dream TV에서 방송되는 교양 프로그램 ‘AI토피아’ 19회에서는 네이버AI랩 윤상두 소장이 지식텔러로 출연해, “AI는 생각하는 척을 하는 것인지, 진짜 스스로 생각하고 있는 것인지”라는 근본적인 질문을 던졌다. 윤상두 소장은 기존 인공지능 모델은 단어의 확률적 연관성만을 계산할 뿐, 문제의 원리나 의미까지는 제대로 이해하지 못한다고 지적했다. 이에 따라 복잡한 수식이나 문맥이 제공될수록 AI가 예상치 못한 답을 제시한다는 점을 언급했다.



“AI는 생각을 흉내낼 뿐일까”…윤상두, ‘AI토피아’서 인간의 사고능력 한계 짚었다→추론모델 시대 조명 / KBSN





반면, 새로운 세대의 AI인 ‘추론모델’이 등장하면서 상황이 달라지고 있다. 윤상두 소장은 “하이클로바X” 등 첨단 AI 기술이 방대한 텍스트 데이터를 학습해, 신속한 답변보다 ‘생각의 과정’ 자체에 중점을 두는 방향으로 진화하고 있음을 알렸다. 또한 추론모델이 실제 서비스에 적용되는 사례로, 최근 온라인상에서 맞춤법을 의도적으로 틀려 번역기의 효율성을 떨어뜨리는 방식이 세간의 관심을 받았음을 설명했다. 기본적인 가이드라인의 중요성을 강조하면서도, “의미 없는 단어를 추려내고 실질적인 해답을 만들어내는 AI의 능력”도 진화 중임을 밝혔다.



윤상두 소장은 그러면서도 “현존하는 거대 언어모델조차 여전히 확률 구조에 의존하고 있다”고 짚었다. 따라서 추론능력을 바탕으로 하더라도 오답을 내놓을 가능성이 남아 있고, 신뢰성과 효율성 사이에서 산업계가 풀어야 할 과제가 여전히 존재함을 지적했다. 특히 “추론이 사고의 깊이를 더하지만, 동시에 상대적으로 많은 자원을 소모한다”며, AI 기술 적용의 경제성 갈등을 언급했다.



진행자 궤도는 “AI가 완벽해질 수는 없지만, 인간보다 실수의 비율이 현저히 낮은 수준까지 왔다는 점이 충분히 의미 있다”고 평가했다. 동시에 “AI만 지나치게 엄격한 기준으로 평가하고 있는 것은 아닌지 생각해 볼 필요가 있다”고 말하며, “AI가 추구할 목표는 인간보다 얼마나 뛰어나게 될 것이냐에 있다”고 덧붙였다. 또 일정 단계를 넘어설 때 AI가 완벽함 자체보다 새로운 가치를 지향할 것이라는 의견을 밝히며 시청자와의 공감을 불러일으켰다.



윤상두 소장은 끝으로 “AI는 여전히 신비로운 존재”라며, “매일 새로운 기술이 등장하고 있기 때문에 ‘AI는 사람처럼 진짜 생각할 수 있을까’라는 질문은 여전히 흥미롭다”고 했다. 대형 AI 지식 교양 프로젝트 ‘AI토피아’는 매주 토요일과 일요일 밤 10시 KBS LIFE와 UHD Dream TV에서 만나볼 수 있으며, 매주 일요일 오전 8시에는 KBS Joy에서도 방영돼 시청자들과 AI의 현재와 미래에 대해 지속적으로 나누고 있다.

external.description:
팬들이 88세에 결혼할 것을 허락한 이찬원이 '편스토랑'서 "50살 밑으로는 여자로 안 보여"라고 충격 발언을 했다.



10월 10일 방송된 KBS 2TV '신상출시 편스토랑'(이하 '편스토랑')에서 찬또셰프 '쿠킹스타' 이찬원은 모교 영남대학교를 찾아 많은 고민을 안고 치열하게 살아가는 후배들을 위해 따뜻한 아침밥을 대접하며 음식을 통해 사랑과 감사를 전하는 '청춘 응원 프로젝트'를 공개했다.



'팬들이 88세에 결혼 허락한 이찬원', '편스토랑'서 "50살 밑으로는 여자로 안 보여" 충격 발언





이날 방송에서 이찬원은 "사실 저도 가수 데뷔를 하지 않았다면 취직이나 미래, 진로에 대한 고민이 정말 많았을 거다. 지금 20대 초반을 겪고 있는 대학생들은 그런 고민이 더욱 클 거다. 그런 후배들한테 따뜻한 밥 한 끼를 해 주고 싶다"라며 무려 250명 후배들을 위해 직접 요리를 하고 배식하는 '찬원의 아침밥'을 준비하며 훈훈함을 자아냈다. 



직접 고기를 하나하나 두드려 250인분 돈가스를 준비하고 열심히 튀기던 이찬원은 조리사님께 "저희 부모님도 식당 일을 하시면서 화상 입은 흔적이 많다. 음식 일이 쉽지 않은 것 같다. 저는 한 달에 평균적으로 두 번 꾸준히 부모님께 밑반찬을 만들어 보낸다"라고 요즘 보기 드문 효자 모습으로 흐뭇함을 선사했다.



이어 상추나물을 무치던 이찬원의 모습을 본 조리사님은 "같이 무치자"며 도움의 손길을 내밀었다. 완성된 상추나물을 시식하고 따봉을 날린 조리사님의 모습에 이찬원은 "나도 하나 줘 봐"라며 반존대 플러팅을 날렸다.



'팬들이 88세에 결혼 허락한 이찬원', '편스토랑'서 "50살 밑으로는 여자로 안 보여" 충격 발언





이 모습을 본 이연복은 "찬원이가 이모들 홀리는 법을 아네"라고 이찬원의 남다른 친화력에 감탄했다. 이에 이찬원은 "나는 나이 50 밑으로는 여자로 안 본다"라며 충격 발언을 해 스튜디오를 뒤집었다. 일례로 이찬원의 팬들은 미래의 희망사항으로 이찬원이 88세에 결혼할 것을 허락했다.



250분이라는 대용량 요리에 처음 도전한 이찬원은 조리사님들과 화기애애한 케미를 보이며 250인분 요리를 무사히 완성하고, 영남대 후배들을 위해 직접 배식까지 한 이찬원은 깜짝 용돈 선물까지 전하며 후배들을 향한 사랑을 전했다.



이와 함께 이찬원은 후배들에게 "항상 고생하시는 어머님들께 박수를 보내 달라"고 말하며 늘 뒤에서 땀 흘리는 조리사들을 향해 감사 인사를 건네고  따뜻함을 자아냈다.



한편, 아직 끝나지 않은 '쿠킹스타' 이찬원의 '청춘 응원 프로젝트' 2부는 오는 10월 17일 금요일 오후 8시 30분 KBS 2TV '편스토랑'에서 방송된다.

record.text: Agentic AI Demands Stronger Digital Trust Systems #AIAgent #AIagentcybersecurity #CyberSecurity

external.description:
As agentic AI becomes more common across industries, companies face a new cybersecurity challenge: how to verify and secure systems that operate independently, make decisions on their own, and appear or disappear without human involvement. 
Consider a financial firm where an AI agent activates early in the morning to analyse trading data, detect unusual patterns, and prepare reports before the markets open. Within minutes, it connects to several databases, completes its task, and shuts down automatically. This type of autonomous activity is growing rapidly, but it raises serious concerns about identity and trust. 
“Many organisations are deploying agentic AI without fully thinking about how to manage the certificates that confirm these systems’ identities,” says Chris Hickman, Chief Security Officer at Keyfactor. 
“The scale and speed at which agentic AI functions are far beyond what most companies have ever managed.” 
AI agents are unlike human users who log in with passwords or devices tied to hardware. They are temporary and adaptable, able to start, perform complex jobs, and disappear without manual authentication. 
This fluid nature makes it difficult to manage digital certificates, which are essential for maintaining trusted communication between systems. 
Greg Wetmore, Vice President of Product Development at Entrust, explains that AI agents act like both humans and machines. 
“When an agent logs into a system or updates data, it behaves like a human user. But when it interacts with APIs or cloud platforms, it looks more like a software component,” he says. 
This dual behaviour requires a flexible security model. AI agents need stable certificates that prove their identity and temporary credentials that control what they are allowed to do. 
These permissions must be revocable in real time if the system behaves unexpectedly.

The challenge becomes even greater when AI agents begin interacting with each other. Without proper cryptographic controls, one system could impersonate another. 
“Once agents start sharing information, certificate management becomes absolutely essential,” Hickman adds. 
Complicating matters further, three major changes are hitting cryptography at once. Certificate lifespans are being shortened to 47 days, post-quantum algorithms are nearing adoption, and organisations must now manage a far larger number of certificates due to AI automation. 
“We’re seeing huge changes in cryptography after decades of stability,” Hickman notes. “It’s a lot to handle for many teams.” 
Keyfactor’s research reveals that almost half of all organisations have not begun preparing for post-quantum encryption, and many still lack a clearly defined role for managing cryptography. 
This lack of governance poses serious risks, especially when certificate management is handled by IT departments without deep security expertise.

Still, experts believe the situation can be managed with existing tools. 
“Agentic AI fits well within established security models such as zero trust,” Wetmore explains. “The technology to issue strong identities, enforce policies, and limit access already exists.” 
According to Sebastian Weir, AI Practice Leader at IBM UK and Ireland, many companies are now focusing on building security into AI projects from the start. 
“While AI development can be up to four times faster, the first version of code often contains many more vulnerabilities...” 
“...Organisations are learning to consider security early instead of adding it later,” he says.
Financial institutions are among those leading the shift, building identity systems that blend the stability of long-term certificates with the flexibility of short-term authorisations. 
Hickman points out that Public Key Infrastructure (PKI) already supports similar scale in IoT environments, managing billions of certificates worldwide. 
He adds, “PKI has always been about scale. The same principles can support agentic AI if implemented properly.”

The real focus now, according to experts, should be on governance and orchestration. 
“Scalability depends on creating consistent and controllable deployment patterns. Orchestration frameworks and governance layers ensure transparency and auditability," says Weir. 
Poorly managed AI agents can cause significant damage. Some have been known to delete vital data or produce false financial information due to misconfiguration.
This makes it critical for companies to monitor agent behaviour closely and apply zero-trust principles where every interaction is verified. 
Securing agentic AI does not require reinventing cybersecurity. It requires applying proven methods to a new, fast-moving environment. 
“We already know that certificates and PKI work. An AI agent can have one certificate for identity and another for authorisation. The key is in how you manage them,” Hickman concludes. 
As businesses accelerate their use of AI, the winners will be those that design trust into their systems from the beginning. By investing in certificate lifecycle management and clear governance, they can ensure that every AI agent operates safely and transparently. Those who ignore this step risk letting their systems act autonomously in the dark, without the trust and control that modern enterprises demand.
external.title: Agentic AI Demands Stronger Digital Trust Systems

record.text: Oura Users Express Concern Over Pentagon Partnership Amid Privacy Debates #Data #DOD #oura

external.description:
Oura, the Finnish company known for its smart health-tracking rings, has recently drawn public attention after announcing a new manufacturing facility in Texas aimed at meeting the needs of the U.S. Department of Defense (DoD). The partnership, which has existed since 2019, became more widely discussed following the August 27 announcement, leading to growing privacy concerns among users.

The company stated that the expansion will allow it to strengthen its U.S. operations and support ongoing defense-related projects. However, the revelation that the DoD is Oura’s largest enterprise customer surprised many users. Online discussions on Reddit and TikTok quickly spread doubts about how user data might be handled under this partnership.

Concerns escalated further when users noticed that Palantir Technologies, a software company known for its government data contracts, was listed as a technology partner in Oura’s enterprise infrastructure. Some users interpreted this connection as a potential risk to personal privacy, particularly those using Oura rings to track reproductive health and menstrual cycles through its integration with the FDA-approved Natural Cycles app.

In response, Oura’s CEO Tom Hale issued a clarification, stating that the partnership does not involve sharing individual user data with the DoD or Palantir. According to the company, the defense platform uses a separate system, and only data from consenting service members can be accessed. Oura emphasized that consumer data and enterprise data are stored and processed independently.

Despite these assurances, some users remain uneasy. Privacy advocates and academics note that health wearables often operate outside strict medical data regulations, leaving gaps in accountability. Andrea Matwyshyn, a professor of law and engineering at Penn State, explained that wearable data can sometimes be repurposed in ways users do not anticipate, such as in insurance or legal contexts.

For many consumers, especially women tracking reproductive health, the issue goes beyond technical safeguards. It reflects growing mistrust of how private companies and governments may collaborate over sensitive biometric data. The discussion also highlights the shifting public attitude toward data privacy, as more users begin to question who can access their most personal information.

Oura maintains that it is committed to protecting user privacy and supporting health monitoring “for all people, including service members.” Still, the controversy serves as a reminder that transparency and accountability remain central to consumer trust in an age where personal data has become one of the most valuable commodities.

record.text: Red Hat Hit by Data Breach, Hackers Exploit GitLab Instance #Cloud #GitHub #GitLab

external.description:
An extortion gang by the name of Crimson Collective claimed to have stolen approximately 570GB of compressed data from internal development repositories belonging to Red Hat. Red Hat confirmed the breach impacted one of its GitLab instances.



The stolen data contains around 800 Customer Engagement Reports (CERs), which contain sensitive data about a customer’s platform and network. A CER is a consulting document made for clients that includes infrastructure data, configuration details, authentication tokens, and other data that could be exploited to attack customer networks. 

Red Hat confirmed that it was hit by a security breach impacting its consulting business, but it has not confirmed any of the threat actor’s claims about the stolen GitLab repositories and customer CERs. 

According to Bleeping Computer’s conversation with the hacker, the breach happened two weeks ago. Threat actors allegedly accessed the full database URIs, authentication tokens, and private data in Red Hat CERs and code. They claim that the data was used to get access to the downstream customer infrastructure.

The hacking gang also released a full directory containing the list of the allegedly extracted GitLab repositories and a list of CERs between 2020 and 2025 on Telegram. 

The directory list of CERs contains various sectors and famous organizations like AT&T, Fidelity, Kaiser, Bank of America, Mayo Clinic,  T-Mobile, Costco, Federal Aviation Administration, the US Navy’s Naval Surface Warfare Center, the House of Representatives, etc. 

The hackers claim they contacted Red Hat with an extortion ransom, but did not get any reply except a message asking the hackers to provide a vulnerability report to Red Hat’s security team.

"We recently detected unauthorized access to a GitLab instance used for internal Red Hat Consulting collaboration in select engagements. Upon detection, we promptly launched a thorough investigation, removed the unauthorized party’s access, isolated the instance, and contacted the appropriate authorities. Our ongoing investigation found that an unauthorized third party had accessed and copied some data from this instance," said Red Hat.
external.title: Red Hat Hit by Data Breach, Hackers Exploit GitLab Instance

external.description:
What if you achieved everything you ever wanted—fame, wealth, genius—and it left you feeling so empty that you had to hide the ropes in your house to keep from ending it all? This isn't a hypothetical. This was the terrifying reality for Leo Tolstoy, one of the greatest writers in history.

Welcome to the podcast that follows a literary giant into the abyss of his existential crisis and back out into the light. At the height of his success, Tolstoy was haunted by one question: what is the meaning of life? His search for an answer drove him through the halls of science and philosophy, but they all came up empty.

The answer, when it finally came, wasn't found in a book or a formula. It was found in the dirt-stained hands and simple faith of peasants. We’ll explore Tolstoy's revolutionary discovery that the true purpose of our existence lies not in what we achieve, but in how we love, serve, and connect with others. This revelation so shattered his world that he gave up his wealth, rejected his status, and dedicated his life to a radical new path of spirituality and compassion.

This isn't just a story about a 19th-century author. It's a timeless roadmap for anyone who has ever felt that there must be more than this.

If you're searching for your own answers, subscribe now. Join us on a journey to find meaning in a world obsessed with the meaningless.
external.title: Rich, Famous, & SUICIDAL: Leo Tolstoy's Search for the Meaning of LIFE

OpenAI 近日舉行 2025 年度開發者大會，推出 AI 版 App Store、AI 助理開發工具，同時端出正式版程式助手 Codex，並發表新模型 API。OpenAI 執行長奧特曼的目標，早已不再是打造最強大 AI 模型，而是試圖從各個角度發力，定義下代人機互動新入口同時，也挑戰手握通路的 Google、Meta 科技巨頭。結合起奧特曼近期和輝達、AMD 結盟，到底 AI 產業下波戰局如何開展？為何 OpenAI 這回工具瞄準企業應用？是否將打破近期許多調查呈現，企業導入 AI 成功機率超低的現象？

「AI已從人們的玩具，轉變為人們日常開發的工具」。

開發者大會，OpenAI執行長奧特曼（Sam Altman）拋出數字，讓聽眾感受AI的巨大進展。2023年，OpenAI每週有200萬名活躍開發者，ChatGPT有1億週活躍用戶（WAU），旗下API每分鐘處理約3億個符元（token）。

時間快轉至今，開發者人數翻倍至400萬人，ChatGPT的週活躍用戶更到8億人，API每分鐘處理的符元數達60個。奧特曼強調，現在正是成為服務與產品創建者（builder）的最佳時機，「從點子到產品實現從未如此迅速」。

### ChatGPT深度整合軟體，是否影響App Store？

此次大會的主軸，圍繞四項相互連結的更新。這些新工具與服務，構成OpenAI從底層模型到上層應用的完整循環，也代表它想更深介入開發者社群。

最受矚目的亮點，是ChatGPT導入原生應用Apps SDK，讓開發者直接介入使用者與AI對話，渲染互動式介面、觸發外部動作，並連接自有資料，觸及8億活躍用戶，對話場景推動創新。

當使用者規劃派對，ChatGPT會建議開啟Spotify建立歌單；當使用者構思產品設計流程，可直接ChatGPT調用Figma，將構想轉為圖表。原先使用者需要打開各自獨立的應用程式，現在進化到ChatGPT一站便即時滿足意圖。

**▲ 使用者可用ChatGPT開啟Canva完成設計工作。（Source：OpenAI）**

### ChatGPT這步棋，要搶蘋果與Google地盤

這步棋除了讓使用者深度綁定ChatGPT，也影響應用程式商店，也就是Google和蘋果的重要營收來源。之前Google和OpenAI都預告用AI購物與支付願景，並發表底層技術協定，如今OpenAI將觸角跨至更多層面，擴張對話向外延伸的行動範圍。

另外一項重要更新，是讓AI代理願景得以落地的Agent Kit。整合視覺化Agent Builder、可嵌入Chat Kit及Evals評估系統，讓開發、測試與部署AI代理的流程更加容易。

開發者可開啟空白白板，拖拉節點設計AI執行任務的邏輯流程，例如先分類用戶意圖，再連接文件搜尋工具，最後加上一道安全防護機制過濾敏感資訊。現場示範僅花8分鐘，就能建立可運作的活動導覽代理，這對企業意義重大，大幅降低導入AI的門檻與複雜性。

許多公司雖然想導入AI代理，但常卡在不知道從哪裡開始才好。Agent Kit內建的安全防護機制與評估系統，能幫助企業驗證AI的可靠性與風險控管，有望加速AI應用從概念驗證走向實際上線。

OpenAI也宣布推出程式開發輔助工具Codex。特色在背後由專為程式碼訓練的GPT-5 Codex模型驅動，並推出新SDK，不再只是被動的程式碼補全工具，而能主動執行複雜任務、甚至整合硬體控制的工程代理。

**▲ 使用者可拖拉打造AI代理，降低技術門檻。（Source：OpenAI）**

不過，Codex面臨的競爭極為激烈，微軟、Google、Anthropic和AWS都有程式開發助理與代理，因此發表Codex時，OpenAI主打合作，因此OpenAI主打深度整合，與Slack、Agent Kit協作，形成完整的開發環境。

此外，OpenAI也同步開放三款新模型API：為金融、法律等高精準度領域設計的GPT-5 Pro；成本更低、反應更快的語音模型Realtime Mini；以及備受期待、能將文字轉為高品質影片的Sora 2預覽版。

### AI原生入口的長期戰場，能否挑戰Google？

在超過8億週活躍使用者的基礎上，OpenAI正從模型供應商轉變為平台經營者。

模型有多聰明固然重要，但現在AI競爭的關鍵在於，將AI智慧轉化成讓開發者創造、分發並獲利的完整生態系。OpenAI有望建立以對話為核心的新入口，只要說出需求，AI就能主動調用合適服務完成任務，勝出關鍵在使用者意圖出現的瞬間。

事實上，這也是Google等面對消費者的軟體巨頭，必須處理的課題。

「Google擁有強大通路優勢，但使用者從搜尋轉向對話，或直接找AI代理，僅將AI嵌入現有產品是否足夠？Google有辦法重新定義接觸使用者的入口嗎？」《遠見》5月Google I/O現場問過執行長皮蔡（Sundar Pichai）這個問題。 對照Google與OpenAI，後者要挑戰Google的主導地位更是一場長征。

Google擁有預設搜尋引擎地位，應用程式更是不知凡幾，累積多年的用戶資料也非OpenAI能比。更關鍵的是，用戶多年形成的搜尋與點擊習慣，短期難以撼動。然OpenAI擁有獨特「AI原生」優勢。沒有歷史包袱，可完全圍繞對話式體驗設計產品，8億用戶正是為AI互動而來，黏性與參與度極高。

反觀Google，雖然能將AI輕易嵌入現有產品，卻也面臨創新者的兩難，過於強大的對話式AI，可能會蠶食搜尋廣告這棵搖錢樹，這或許會使顛覆性創新步伐有所遲疑。

**▲ 貿然轉向AI生成結果，可能危及Google廣告收入，不過5月Google I/O已看出Google放手一搏的企圖心。（Source：Google）**

因此，與其說這是正面衝突，不如說是OpenAI正憑著靈活性，在Google巨大版圖外尋覓突破點，迫使產業重新思考AI時代入口的模樣。

### ChatGPT將變成懂賺企業財的助理

對一般用戶而言，短期最明顯改變，是ChatGPT將更強大實用，不只是聊天夥伴，逐漸轉變成熟悉脈絡、按照需求完成任務的超級助理。長期來看，從電商客服到銀行App，各種應用都會更聰明更懂你，數位體驗全面升級。

綜觀這次開發者大會，OpenAI想傳達的核心訊息十分明確，真正競爭不在技術突破，而在能否把技術轉化為讓開發者與企業都能參與的生態。奧特曼把籌碼押注AI代理與對話將定義軟體未來的信念，同時不斷尋找新流量與使用者入口。只是，沒有清楚深刻的護城河，對手也能快速跟上，這是OpenAI的隱憂。

OpenAI發起的平台競賽，才正要開始。
